HEADWORD: Convallamarin
<hw>Con*val`la*ma"rin</hw>
<pr>(k⟦ocr⟧n*v⟦acr⟧l`l⟦adot⟧*m⟦amac⟧"r⟦icr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Convallaria</ets> + L. <ets>amarus</ets> bitter.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A white, crystalline, poisonous substance,
regarded as a glucoside, extracted from the lily of the valley
(<spn>Convallaria Majalis</spn>). Its taste is first bitter, then
sweet.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Convallaria</ent>⟦br⟧
